</div>
			<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Statistical Accounts of Scotland</h1>
									<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
									<div id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
								<div id="contentSub"></div>
												<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
					Jump to:					<a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, 					<a href="#p-search">search</a>
				</div>
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:162px;"><a href="/wiki/File:O.S.A._book_spine_title.JPG" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f5/O.S.A._book_spine_title.JPG/160px-O.S.A._book_spine_title.JPG" width="160" height="149" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f5/O.S.A._book_spine_title.JPG/240px-O.S.A._book_spine_title.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f5/O.S.A._book_spine_title.JPG/320px-O.S.A._book_spine_title.JPG 2x" data-file-width="2284" data-file-height="2128" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:O.S.A._book_spine_title.JPG" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>
Old Statistical Account</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>The <i><b>Statistical Accounts of Scotland</b></i> are a series of documentary publications, related in subject matter though published at different times, covering life in Scotland in the 18th, 19th and 20th centuries.</p>
<p>The <i>Old (or First) Statistical Account of Scotland</i> was published between 1791 and 1799 by <a href="/wiki/Sir_John_Sinclair" title="Sir John Sinclair" class="mw-redirect">Sir John Sinclair of Ulbster</a>. The <i>New (or Second) Statistical Account of Scotland</i> published under the auspices of the <a href="/wiki/General_Assembly_of_the_Church_of_Scotland" title="General Assembly of the Church of Scotland">General Assembly of the Church of Scotland</a> between 1834 and 1845. These first two Statistical Accounts of Scotland are among the finest European contemporary records of life during the <a href="/wiki/Scottish_Agricultural_Revolution" title="Scottish Agricultural Revolution">agricultural</a> and <a href="/wiki/Industrial_Revolution" title="Industrial Revolution">industrial revolutions</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-EDINA_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-EDINA-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>A <i>Third Statistical Account of Scotland</i> was published between 1951 and 1992.</p>
<p></p>
